<div id="feedbackTextContainer">
				 <p id="feedbackText" class="ltrStyle mCustomScrollbar _mCS_7" dir="ltr" style="overflow: hidden;"><div class="mCustomScrollBox mCS-dark" id="mCSB_7" style="position: relative; height: 100%; overflow: hidden; max-width: 100%; max-height: 487px;"><div class="mCSB_container mCS_no_scrollbar" style="position:relative; top:0;"><p align="center"><strong>中国饭</strong> <strong>Chinese Food</strong></p>中国饭 covers all varieties of Chinese food in different styles. There are, aside from<img border="0" hspace="0" alt="中国饭" src="https://gloss.dliflc.edu/products/gloss/cm_soc434/Images/cm_434_Chinese-food,-sina.gif" align="right" _src="https://gloss.dliflc.edu/products/gloss/cm_soc434/Images/cm_434_Chinese-food,-sina.gif"> numerous minor styles, four principle schools of Chinese cuisine (四大菜系): 
<p></p>
<ul>
<li>
<div align="left"><em>Cantonese cuisine</em> - 粤菜 (yuècài)</div>
</li><li>
<div align="left"><em>Sichuan cuisine</em> - 川菜 (chuāncài)</div>
</li><li>
<div align="left"><em>Shandong cuisine</em> - 鲁菜 (lǔcài)</div>
</li><li>
<div align="left"><em>Huaiyang cuisine</em> - 淮阳菜 (huáiyángcài)</div></li></ul>
<p align="left">A Chinese restaurant usually specialized in only one of those cooking styles, but some are more eclectic and syncretic.</p>
<p align="left">For a Chinese meal, rice, sometimes substituted by noodles or dumplings, is the <strong>主食</strong> (zhǔshí, <em>staple food</em>). Everything else is called <strong>副食</strong> (fùshí, <em>non-staple food</em>).</p>
<p align="left">Chinese cooking emphasizes flavor, color, aroma, and presentation. Here are the main flavors in Chinese cuisine: <strong>辣</strong> (là, <em>spicy</em>); <strong>甜</strong> (tián, <em>sweet</em>); <strong>咸</strong> (xián, <em>salty</em>); <strong>酸</strong> (suān, <em>sour</em>); <strong>苦</strong> (kǔ, <em>bitter</em>).</p>
<p align="left"></p></div><div class="mCSB_scrollTools" style="position: absolute; display: none;"><div class="mCSB_draggerContainer"><div class="mCSB_dragger" style="position: absolute; top: 0px;" oncontextmenu="return false;"><div class="mCSB_dragger_bar" style="position:relative;"></div></div><div class="mCSB_draggerRail"></div></div></div></div></p>
